**Tests (table-driven over synthetic manifests in a temp git repo):**
Harness mirrors internal/replay/resolve_test.go (initRepo + git init/config, then
`runmanifest.Writer{Store}.Write` per run, `makeManifest`/`makeStage` style builders)
— that harness is package-private to replay, so copy the minimal helpers into the bench
test file (set distinct `Created` via the Manifest builder; build pointer inputs/outputs
with `Storage: artifactstore.StoragePointer`). Note makeStage uses a 40-char lowercase
hex GitSHA (strings.Repeat("a",40)) — a VALID OID, so it doubles as the passing-sha case.
Cases:
 - qualifying single run selected; Stage/Commit/Created populated correctly (valid 40-hex sha).
 - ordering: 3 runs, Created out of insertion order -> Selected is Created DESC.
 - tie-break: two runs equal Created -> RunID DESC ordering deterministic.
 - last truncation: 5 qualifying, last=2 -> 2 most-recent selected, rest absent from Selected.
 - last larger than available -> all returned, no error.
 - last <= 0 -> ErrInvalidLast.
 - skip: missing stage / ambiguous stage / empty GitSHA (-> no-git-sha) / pointer input /
   pointer output -> each produces the right SkipReason + Detail and is excluded from Selected.
 - skip: MALFORMED git_sha [ATTEMPT-2] -> SkipInvalidGitSHA, NOT selected. Subcases to
   cover the format rule: "xyz" (non-hex), 39-char hex (wrong length), and an uppercase
   40-char hex (case rule). NOTE: such a stage is structurally valid per
   runmanifest.Validate, so it CAN be written via Writer; build it directly with the bad
   GitSHA. Also keep a 40-char lowercase-hex stage as the explicit PASSING case.
 - zero runs in repo -> empty result, nil error.
 - zero qualifying (all skipped) -> empty Selected, Skipped populated, nil error.
 - parse error: write a junk manifest.json into a run ref -> SelectCohort errors naming the run.
 - mixed cohort: qualifying + skipped interleaved -> only qualifying selected, all skips recorded.

**Docs:** None for this slice — internal library, no user surface yet. User docs
(docs/bench.md) land with the CLI bead (.4); root.go rootLong stays unchanged here.

**Risks:** None significant. Predicate is a faithful subset of what replay can actually
execute (no new git/runner machinery; the sha-format rule mirrors worktree.validateSHA).
Keep the predicate in lockstep with replay+worktree so .2 never hits a "qualified-but-
fails-to-replay" run; documented inline by referencing the replay.go / worktree.go line
each check mirrors.

